race.comment: JAMROCK (1) hasn't delivered lately but the market's kept him safe and this looks a race he can bounce in. The 2kg claim of Hutchinson comes in handy and the soft deck is right up his alley. Looks well placed now and can put his best foot forward. I LOVE THIS SONG (6) closed strongly last start at Manangatang but couldn't reel in the winner when beaten 2L. Back in trip slightly today, but she looks right in this off the figures she produced last time out. Can make her presence felt. NIGHT CRUISER (7) won fresh then flopped but gets back to a winning distance. Claimer gets him in low at the weights. Have to respect. MR TRAFFICANTI (2) is building nicely and could sneak into the minors.
